President Obama expressed his sadness over the loss of life and damage caused by Super Typhoon Yolanda in the Philippines. He acknowledged the resilience of the Filipino people and their spirit of Bayanihan, a term referring to the community's collective effort to help one another. The United States has already provided substantial humanitarian aid and is prepared to continue assisting the Philippine government in their relief and recovery efforts. The President's thoughts and prayers are with the millions affected by this catastrophic storm.